Digital lender Tala has announced the access of Ksh.16.08 billion ($145 million) in additional startup funding. The new disbursements bring’s the fintech’s total funding to more than Ksh.38.82 billion ($350 million) from partners including new investors Kindred Ventures and J. Safra Group. Tala’s original pool of investors meanwhile includes the Stellar Development Foundation, IVP, Revolution Growth, Lowercase Capital and PayPal Ventures. The digital only lender is expected to deploy proceeds from the fundraiser to innovate its lending platform to include new savings and credit tools. Tala further plans to tap the new capital for geography and product expansion to include crypto offerings. Tala is presently available in Kenya, the Philippines, Mexico and India. Also Read: The company estimates to have disbursed loans worth more than Ksh.299 billion ($2.7) billion to more than six million customers in the four markets since launching seven years ago in Nairobi. The new capital boost represents series E funding which is mainly leveraged by startups who seek to stay private longer or are yet to meet their expectations. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam